definitions.definition: A device for winding thread onto a spool .
A program or process that spools (places data in a queue to be accessed later)
examples: The print spooler sends each page to the printer when it is ready for it.

main_definition: ( textiles ) A device for winding thread onto a spool .
secondary_definitions: ( computing ) A program or process that spools (places data in a queue to be accessed later)
